FAQs 
1. What are the language requirements for study medicine in Hungary?
Most medical programs in Hungary are taught in English. Proficiency in English is typically required, and you may need to submit TOEFL or IELTS scores. Some universities also offer preparatory language courses for students who need to improve their English skills.

2. Are there scholarships available for international students in Hungary?
Yes, many universities in Hungary offer scholarships to international students based on academic merit, financial need, or other criteria. These scholarships can help cover tuition fees and living expenses.

3. How much does it cost to live in Hungary as a student?
The cost of living in Hungary is relatively low compared to other European countries. On average, students might spend between €400 to €800 per month on accommodation, food, transportation, and leisure activities.
